<p>Guatemala is mourning after attacks linked to gangs left 10 police officers dead, following unrest tied to coordinated prison disturbances. President Bernardo Arévalo’s government moved to tighten security and Congress approved an emergency declaration as authorities try to contain violence and restore control. The crisis adds pressure to Arévalo’s wider push against organized crime and corruption, as officials seek to prevent further escalation while keeping daily life functioning.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/gOrgNn6bGE0-zr-87iU7ihjc1f2wHcqSavJHSC7wehRBVOlNCJrVPONMtm8Vz8U_zNffDVui-XVreQPBWTim9eMKh_TSL3X7CYiTKw_-wJ3l2tE9206N0qWbIDiRzYcFruMoGhDECI5Hm9kpkbZYTnkpsGaeGr2KDTlYZJOhW27XLaRqGND3QBixeyyDGhxa1sd3pA' alt='A ceremony to honor police officers killed in attacks, held Monday in Guatemala City.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Prison takeover: The violence began Saturday when inmates seized control of three prisons in apparently coordinated riots and took 43 guards hostage, according to reporting from Guatemala.</li><li>Arrest powers: The state of emergency allows police to arrest suspected criminals without a judicial order, a step the government says is aimed at quickly disrupting gang activity.</li><li>Injured officers: Beyond those killed, a dozen officers were reported injured in the attacks, underscoring the scale of the assault on law enforcement.</li><li>Street security: Residents saw heavier security on the streets and some rights were curtailed after Congress approved the emergency declaration requested by President Bernardo Arévalo.</li><li>Political test: The prison uprisings and killings present another challenge for Arévalo as he confronts organized crime while pursuing an anti-corruption agenda.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Guatemalan government: Officials say emergency measures and heightened deployments are intended to reassert control and respond rapidly to gang-linked violence. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/9-guatemalan-police-officers-dead-after-gang-attacks-129350972'>ABC News</a>)</li><li>Security authorities under the emergency decree: Police are empowered to arrest suspected criminals without first obtaining a judicial order under the state of emergency. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/20/guatemala-mourns-10-police-slain-by-gangsters-amid-state-of-emergency'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>President Bernardo Arévalo’s administration: The unrest is framed as a direct test of the president’s efforts to curb organized crime alongside his broader anti-corruption drive. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/01/19/world/americas/death-toll-rises-in-guatemalan-gang-riots.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/9-guatemalan-police-officers-dead-after-gang-attacks-129350972'>9 Guatemalan police officers dead after gang attacks</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/20/guatemala-mourns-10-police-slain-by-gangsters-amid-state-of-emergency'>Guatemala mourns 10 police slain by gangsters amid state of emergency</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/guatemala-gang-violence-prison-takeover-emergency-declared-several-killed-january-20-2026/article70527859.ece'>State of emergency declared after death toll rises to nine in gangsters&#x27; attacks on Guatemalan police</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/01/19/world/americas/death-toll-rises-in-guatemalan-gang-riots.html'>Death Toll Rises in Guatemalan Gang Riots</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20260119-ninth-policeman-dies-in-guatemala-gang-riots-attacks'>A ninth policeman succumbs to his injuries from prison riots and attacks on police officers in Guatemala. A dozen officers were also injured in the attacks, and a state of emergency has been declared.</a> - france24.com</li></ul>